 <div style="width: 240px; padding: 0.4em; position: relative; margin-left: -5px; margin-top: 70px; display: inline-block"> The kromeri or <i>cromeri</i> were street vendors, who practiced their trade from November to April, selling fabrics and small items required to rural life, especially in isolated houses in Tyrolean, Austrian, Bavarian, Bohemian and Trentino countryside. This job is almost entirely disappeared we still have some in the valleys of South Tyrol.<br>The typical container of the kromeri's products was a wooden box that was transported in shoulder, it has a lot of drawers of various sizes, and it was used as both exhibitors and to sit.
